# NSE Dashboard — Backlog

## BUG-001 · Sector PE shows negative (-204.4x) in Steam Gauge valuation panel
**Severity:** medium (visible, misleads the valuation read; does not corrupt data)
**Where:** steam.html — Buffett/Steam "Valuation stretch" panel; sector-PE aggregation (Upstox key-ratios `sectorPE`, or a local aggregate).
**Observed:** HAPPSTMNDS (IT), 2026-07-23 — panel showed "Sector avg PE: -204.4x" and EPS "—". A negative sector PE is nonsensical.
**Root cause (hypothesis):** simple-mean aggregation of constituent P/Es (or aggregate price ÷ aggregate EPS) where one or more loss-making constituents carry negative or near-zero EPS. A single large-negative or near-zero-EPS name drags a mean PE negative or explodes it. Universe expansion made this more frequent (more constituents per sector → higher chance of a loss-maker in the bucket).
**Fix options (in order of preference):**
1. **Exclude non-positive-earnings constituents** from the sector-PE aggregate (standard index practice — negative-PE names are simply dropped from the PE calc).
2. Use **median** constituent PE instead of mean (robust to outliers and loss-makers).
3. If using aggregate price/earnings, **floor aggregate EPS at a small positive** and flag as "n/m" (not meaningful) when the pool has too few positive-earnings names.
**Additional:** when sector PE is unavailable/not-meaningful, show "n/m" rather than a negative number, and skip the "PE X is reasonable vs sector Y" sentence.
**Effort:** small — isolated to the sector-PE computation + one display guard. Node-testable in a stub with a loss-maker fixture.
**Independent of:** universe expansion. Can be done any time.

## FEATURE-001 · Single source of truth for the universe (steam ← Indicators)
**Context:** steam.html STOCK_MASTER (717) and Indicators UNIVERSE (798) are hand-maintained and drift (found ~52-name drift during Tranche 1). 
**Proposal:** steam.html fetches its universe from the Indicators `?action=universe` route at load; UNIVERSE constant becomes the single canon. Eliminates drift permanently.
**Effort:** small-medium. Deferred — nice-to-have, not blocking.

